  "text": "The YGTSS is a semi-structured clinical interview designed to assess current tic severity; this scale yields three summary scores; total motor (0-25), total phonic (0-25), and total tic (sum of motor and phonic) scores. The YGTTS also contains an impairment scale (0-50), which evaluates the global level of functional impairment arising from tics [CITATION_1] . Because this study was designed to compare efficacy in reducing tic symptoms, the primary outcome measure was total tic score. The YGTSS was administered to each subject at each visit.",
